    "body": "newer LuaJit introduceds a \"String Buffer\" (ext_buffer) concept: https://github.com/LuaJIT/LuaJIT/commit/a119497becdf2894fb7fa737f106464309dd7947\r\n\r\n[docs](https://github.com/LuaJIT/LuaJIT/blob/a119497becdf2894fb7fa737f106464309dd7947/doc/ext_buffer.html)\r\n\r\n> The string buffer library allows high-performance manipulation of string-like data.\r\n>\r\n> Unlike Lua strings, which are constants, string buffers are mutable sequences of 8-bit (binary-transparent) characters. Data can be stored, formatted and encoded into a string buffer and later converted, extracted or decoded.\r\n>\r\n> ... In conjunction with the FFI library, they allow zero-copy operations.\r\n>\r\n> The string buffer libary also includes a high-performance serializer for Lua objects.\r\n\r\ncan we map this to Vim \"blob\" type?\r\n\r\nbesides performance, it has ring-buffer behavior:\r\n\r\n> The buffer space that holds the characters is managed automaticallyâ€”it grows as needed and already consumed space is recycled. Use `buffer.new(size)` and `buf:free()`, if you need more\r\ncontrol.\r\n\r\n",
